oughout Europe and in the Ottoman Empire. They were thus major players in France’s and Europe’s industrialisation and the modernisation of its banking system. This book is equally a social and cultural history of the Jews in France, addressing the means through which the Pereires managed their business empire and the contribution of family life to its success. It is their first full-scale biography in English.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aBusinesspeoplezFrancevBiography. 0aIndustrialistszFrancevBiography. 0aJewish businesspeoplezFrancevBiography. 7aHISTORY / Europe / France.2bisacsh  aEmile.  aIsaac Pereire.  aJudaism.  aSaint-Simonianism.  abusiness practices.  afamily business.  ainvestment capital.  anineteenth-century France.  apartnership.  apolitical allegiance.  arailway entrepreneurs.  asocialism.1 aDavies, Helen M., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packagez978311128357940uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152611095440uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526110954423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526110954/original  a978-3-11-128357-9  Manchester University Press 2014 eBook-Packageb2014  aGBV-deGruyter-alles